      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "🪄 **Cliplet v0.2.0 – Canonical Encryption & Stable Format**\r\n\r\n### 🔒 Major Update: New Encryption System\r\nCliplet’s encryption system has been rebuilt.  \r\nThis update replaces the previous experimental key handling with a stable, vault-wide encryption format based on your `vaultId`.\r\n\r\n- Replaced seed-based key generation with a consistent vault-level key (`vaultId`)\r\n- Removed legacy and migration logic from earlier test builds\r\n- Added `schemaVersion` and `pluginVersion` to `data.json` for clearer version tracking\r\n- Unified encryption behavior across Desktop and Mobile\r\n- Simplified backend initialization and improved reliability\r\n\r\n> 🧭 Existing data from early builds before **v0.2.0** will be cleared automatically  \r\n> to prevent compatibility issues.  \r\n> After updating, please restart Obsidian and re-add your snippets.\r\n\r\nThis marks the first **stable data format** that will be maintained going forward.  \r\nFuture updates will build upon this canonical encryption scheme.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 🧩 Other Improvements\r\n- Refined internal architecture — `ClipletService` now owns backend lifecycle management  \r\n- Simplified JSON/IDB backends and removed redundant seed/meta stores  \r\n- Minor internal cleanup and stability fixes\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 🙏 A note to early testers\r\nThanks to everyone who tried the early public builds before the official release.  \r\nYour feedback made it possible to finalize Cliplet’s encryption and storage design early.  \r\nThis version lays the foundation for upcoming features such as password protection and enhanced snippet organization.",
      "downloadCount": 40,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "0.2.0",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2025-10-14T12:51:56Z",
      "tag": "0.2.0"
    },
